About Terraform providers.-> A Terraform provider is a plugin that lets Terraform communicate with a specific platform (like AWS, Azure, Google, etc.).
Terraform file which is in HCL language (.tf ) file ->> terraform in our system
Convert out .tf file to aws understanding code --> aws provider
this converted file will call aws api -->> like calling s3 api
even doing through manual console way creating infra will also api.

          ┌────────────────────────────┐
          │   Your .tf File (HCL)      │
          │ Infrastructure as Code     │
          └──────────────┬─────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
          ┌────────────────────────────┐
          │      Terraform CLI         │
          │  (terraform init/plan/apply) │
          └──────────────┬─────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
          ┌────────────────────────────┐
          │      Terraform Provider     │
          │  (AWS / Azure / GCP Plugin) │
          └──────────────┬─────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
         ┌──────────────────────────────┐
         │  Provider Converts HCL Code   │
         │   into Cloud-Understandable   │
         │           API Calls           │
         └──────────────┬───────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
      ┌────────────────────────────────────┐
      │        AWS API Endpoints           │
      │ (Example: EC2 API, S3 API, VPC API)│
      └──────────────────┬─────────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
      ┌────────────────────────────────────┐
      │      AWS Creates Infrastructure     │
      │ (EC2, S3, VPC, SG, IAM, etc.)       │
      └────────────────────────────────────┘
